Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta is cooking, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} into 3 pieces widthways. When the pasta has been cooking for about 8 mins, add the Tenderstem® to the pasta and water and bring back to the boil. Cook with the pasta for the last ~{4%minutes} of cooking time.

When the pasta and broccoli are cooked, drain them in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} to stop them sticking together, leave the colander in the sink.

Pop your pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g}, @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Reduce the heat slightly then add the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Pour in the @water for the sauce{50%ml}, bring to the boil and simmer for ~{2%minutes}. Remove from the heat. Stir in the @truffle zest{1%tsp} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Add the pasta and broccoli to the sauce and toss together. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Serve in #bowls{}, sprinkle over the @walnuts{20} and enjoy!

> If you've decided to add diced chicken breast to your meal, add the chicken to the pan with the mushrooms and cook.